    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='Based on the provided excerpts from the Amazon 2025 Form 10-K, here is a synthesis of all disclosures specifically related to **Project Kuiper** and its associated satellite infrastructure. The information is integrated across multiple notes and sections.\n\n### **1. Accounting Treatment & Expense Recognition**\n*   **Current Expensing:** The company "currently expense[s] the majority of the costs associated with the development of [its] satellite network for global broadband service." This includes:\n    *   Production costs\n    *   Launch costs\n    *   Payroll costs\n    *   **Launch service deposits**, which are expensed upon the occurrence of the launch.\n*   **Future Capitalization:** The company states it will "capitalize certain of these costs once the service achieves **commercial viability, including sales to customers**."\n*   **Balance Sheet Classification (Pre-Capitalization):** Costs such as **satellite network launch services deposits** are classified within **"Other assets"** on the consolidated balance sheets. Upon achieving commercial viability, these will be reclassified to **"Construction in progress"** within **"Property and equipment, net."**\n\n### **2. Capital Expenditure & Investment Context**\n*   While **Project Kuiper is not broken out as a separate line item** in the capex tables, it is a key component of Amazon\'s overarching strategic investment.\n*   The company explicitly links its massive infrastructure spending to supporting initiatives "including the development of a satellite network for global broadband service."\n*   The significant year-over-year increases in **"Total net additions to property and equipment"**—particularly within the **AWS segment** ($96.5 billion in 2025)—reflect the scale of investment in technology infrastructure, which encompasses satellite-related assets.\n\n### **3. Regulatory Milestone & Commitment**\n*   A specific **Federal Communications Commission (FCC) milestone** is disclosed as a